1. Fork a repo and clone to local

2. git config --global user.name  **

3. git config --global user.mail  **

4. Config remote for the fork
git remote -v
git remote add upstream https://github.com/ORIGINAL_OWNER/ORIGINAL_REPOSITORY.git
git remote -v

5. Sync the fork
git fetch upstream
git checkout master
git merge upstream/master





Reference:
1.https://help.github.com/articles/syncing-a-fork/
2.https://help.github.com/articles/configuring-a-remote-for-a-fork/
3. Useful Notes about pull request
http://www.soimort.org/posts/149/
